‚Ä¢ Linux: ps, lsof, netstat, systemctl, journalctl


üîç Process Tree Analysis

Get-Process | Sort-Object CPU -Descending
Get-Process | Sort CPU -Descending | Select -First 20

Get-WinEvent -LogName "Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational" | Select-String "ParentProcessId"
Get-WinEvent -FilterHashtable @{LogName='Security'; StartTime=(Get-Date).AddHours(-1)} -MaxEvents 200


üì° Network Connections

Windows
netstat -ano | findstr ESTABLISHED
Get-NetTCPConnection | Where-Object {$_.State -eq "Established"}
Get-NetTCPConnection | Sort-Object -Property State

Linux
netstat -tulpen
lsof -i


üì° Services

Get-Service | Where-Object {$_.Status -eq 'Running'}


üßæ Event Log Review

Get-WinEvent -LogName Security | where {$_.Id -eq 4624 -or $_.Id -eq 4625}
Get-WinEvent -LogName "Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon/Operational"


üßæ Scheduled Tasks

Get-ScheduledTask | where {$_.State -ne 'Disabled'}










